1
00:02:57,605 --> 00:02:59,409
好了
There you go.

2
00:03:01,607 --> 00:03:04,810
当时你饿了
There. You were hungry.

3
00:03:23,295 --> 00:03:25,463
就是这样
That's it.

4
00:04:16,349 --> 00:04:17,950
重复
Repeat.

5
00:04:46,447 --> 00:04:48,280
先生 您好
Good day, sir.

6
00:04:48,415 --> 00:04:49,647
祝您今天愉快
Good day to you.

7
00:04:49,782 --> 00:04:52,750
您来休兰兹做什么事？
What brings you to Hewlands?

8
00:04:52,885 --> 00:04:54,451
我正在给这些男孩们补习
I'm tutoring the boys here.

9
00:04:54,586 --> 00:04:56,588
拉丁语家教
The Latin tutor.

10
00:04:56,724 --> 00:04:58,990
我听说过你
I've heard of you.

11
00:05:04,996 --> 00:05:07,306
是什么把你吸引到花园里来？
What brought you into the garden?

12
00:05:09,339 --> 00:05:12,003
呃……
Uh...

13
00:05:12,138 --> 00:05:14,339
这只是个问题 老师
It's just a question, master tutor.

14
00:05:14,475 --> 00:05:16,172
是的 我 呃……
Yes, I, uh...

15
00:05:17,617 --> 00:05:20,810
我想这里的空气一定很清新 而且……
I suppose the air was fresh out here, and...

16
00:05:20,946 --> 00:05:24,222
呃 我看到你和你的鸟在一起了
uh, I saw you with your bird.

17
00:05:24,358 --> 00:05:26,655
——是只鹰——啊
- It's a hawk. - Ah.

18
00:05:29,092 --> 00:05:30,659
我可以？
May I?

19
00:05:44,474 --> 00:05:46,642
不要靠得太近
Don't get too close.

20
00:05:47,510 --> 00:05:49,381
他不认识你
He doesn't know you.

21
00:05:55,650 --> 00:05:57,048
哦
Oh.

22
00:05:58,183 --> 00:06:00,524
你好 男孩
Hello, boy.

23
00:06:05,966 --> 00:06:09,159
啊
Ah.

24
00:06:09,995 --> 00:06:12,294
他喜欢你
He likes you.

25
00:06:15,305 --> 00:06:17,134
你叫什么名字？
What is your name?

26
00:06:18,805 --> 00:06:20,306
我不会告诉你
I shan't tell you.

27
00:06:23,048 --> 00:06:24,878
你必须这样做
You shall.

28
00:06:28,780 --> 00:06:30,254
我不会
I shan't.

29
00:06:30,389 --> 00:06:32,655
你应该这么做——我不会
- You shall. - I won't.

30
00:06:35,658 --> 00:06:37,891
等我们接吻的时候你就会告诉我了
You'll tell me when we kiss.

31
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,912
你在干什么？
What are you doing?

32
00:07:17,035 --> 00:07:18,267
艾格尼丝
Agnes.

33
00:07:21,371 --> 00:07:23,398
我的名字叫艾格尼丝
My name is Agnes.

34
00:07:24,573 --> 00:07:26,610
你从哪来？
Where are you from?

35
00:07:30,612 --> 00:07:32,775
我说错话了吗？
Have I said something?

36
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:34,477
- 啊？ - 不
- Huh? - No.

37
00:07:35,547 --> 00:07:37,715
你不知道我是谁——等等 我想见见……
- You don't know who I am. - Wait, I wish to see...

38
00:07:37,851 --> 00:07:39,790
你再也见不到我了
You can't see me again.

39
00:07:39,926 --> 00:07:41,493
哦
Oh.

40
00:07:47,926 --> 00:07:50,061
你去哪儿了？
Where have you been?

41
00:07:50,197 --> 00:07:51,597
我当时在田里帮巴塞洛缪干活
I was in the field helping Bartholomew.

42
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:53,237
一只刚出生的小羊羔生病了
A newborn lamb is unwell.

43
00:07:53,372 --> 00:07:55,501
嗯 我……我去了田野
Well, I... I went to the field.

44
00:07:55,637 --> 00:07:57,267
我没在那里看到你
I did not see you there.

45
00:07:57,402 --> 00:08:01,275
我当时也在场告诉她 巴塞洛缪
Well, I was there. Tell her, Bartholomew.

46
00:08:01,411 --> 00:08:02,778
她当时就在那里
She was there.

47
00:08:02,913 --> 00:08:04,940
你见过那位新来的拉丁语家教吗？
Have you seen the new Latin tutor?

48
00:08:05,075 --> 00:08:06,584
手套匠的儿子
The glover's son.

49
00:08:06,719 --> 00:08:09,310
男孩们说他突然跑出去 就再也没回来
The boys said he just ran out, never returned.

50
00:08:09,446 --> 00:08:10,816
他本应该给他们上课的
He was supposed to give them lessons

51
00:08:10,951 --> 00:08:12,849
为了偿还他父亲的债务
to pay off his father's debts.

52
00:08:12,985 --> 00:08:14,083
我没见过他
I haven't seen him.

53
00:08:14,218 --> 00:08:15,854
唉 我真应该更谨慎些
Well, should've known better.

54
00:08:15,990 --> 00:08:18,160
有其父必有其子
Like father, like son.

55
00:08:22,336 --> 00:08:23,962
你知道 我确实相信你是
You know, I do believe you are

56
00:08:24,097 --> 00:08:25,337
教区里最漂亮的女孩们
the prettiest girls in the parish.

57
00:08:25,472 --> 00:08:26,868
我们是总有一天
-We are. -One day,

58
00:08:27,003 --> 00:08:28,463
我会保持头脑清醒
I shall have my wits about me

59
00:08:28,598 --> 00:08:30,467
献给所有前来追求你的人
for all the suitors that will come for you.

60
00:08:30,603 --> 00:08:33,008
艾格尼丝是老大 她会第一个结婚
Agnes is the eldest. She'll marry first.

61
00:08:33,144 --> 00:08:35,639
如果她继续往森林里跑 她就不会成功
She will not if she keeps running off to the forest

62
00:08:35,775 --> 00:08:37,646
像吉普赛人一样
like a gypsy.

63
00:09:07,709 --> 00:09:08,742
你去哪儿了？
Where have you been?

64
00:09:08,877 --> 00:09:10,510
我们几个小时前就该见到你了
We were expecting you hours ago.

65
00:09:10,646 --> 00:09:11,741
我当时……嗯？
- I was... - Well?

66
00:09:11,877 --> 00:09:12,841
我当时在工作
I was working.

67
00:09:12,976 --> 00:09:15,378
坐下坐下
Sit. Sit.

68
00:09:17,291 --> 00:09:19,250
你的晚餐快凉了
Your supper's near cold.

69
00:09:20,691 --> 00:09:22,017
- 呃 孩子们 孩子们！ - 嘿 - 停
- Uh, boys, boys! - Hey. -Stop.

70
00:09:22,153 --> 00:09:24,086
足够所有人享用
There's enough for all.

71
00:09:24,221 --> 00:09:25,989
在休兰兹的课程进行得怎么样？
How go the lessons at Hewlands?

72
00:09:26,124 --> 00:09:27,732
那些男孩都不是学者
Those boys are no scholars.

73
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:29,933
我对学习这些东西感到好奇——嗯
I wonder at the notion of all that learning. -Hmm.

74
00:09:30,068 --> 00:09:32,736
拉丁语中指那些注定只能当牧羊人的男孩
Latin for boys who will be naught but sheep farmers.

75
00:09:32,871 --> 00:09:35,000
这是装腔作势——不 不 不！
- It is the putting on of airs. - No, no, no!

76
00:09:35,136 --> 00:09:36,700
——这样就可以了！——好的 吉尔伯特
- That will do! - All right, Gilbert.

77
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:41,613
你听你妈妈说了 资源足够所有人用
You heard your mother. There's enough for all.

78
00:09:43,574 --> 00:09:46,140
你诋毁休兰兹的男孩们
You speak ill of the boys at Hewlands.

79
00:09:46,276 --> 00:09:48,147
“他们根本不是学者”
"They're no scholars."

80
00:09:49,147 --> 00:09:50,678
但我告诉你
But I tell you something,

81
00:09:50,813 --> 00:09:52,151
他们永远比你更有男子气概
they'll ever be more of a man than you are.

82
00:09:52,286 --> 00:09:54,790
他们从事的是正当的工作 不像你
They are put to honest work, unlike you.

83
00:09:54,925 --> 00:09:58,630
你那副浮夸的样子 毫无用处 毫无价值
Useless, tradeless, your fancy airs.

84
00:09:59,596 --> 00:10:00,960
所有这些教育
All that education,

85
00:10:01,095 --> 00:10:03,327
毫无道理可言
not an ounce of sense.

86
00:10:04,328 --> 00:10:05,735
我辅导那些男孩是为了赚钱
I'm tutoring those boys to pay

87
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:07,972
你欠那家人的债 对吧？
your debts to that family, am I not?

88
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:11,407
你对那个家庭欠下了无法估量的债务
Your immeasurable amount of debt to that family.

89
00:10:11,543 --> 00:10:13,711
我不是…… —— 住手！
- I'm not... - Stop!

90
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:20,751
那么 休兰兹庄园的其他家庭成员呢？你见过他们吗？
What of the rest of the family at Hewlands? Have you met them?

91
00:10:21,748 --> 00:10:22,883
只有母亲
The mother only.

92
00:10:23,018 --> 00:10:24,921
- 不是大女儿吗？ - 不是
- Not the eldest daughter? - No.

93
00:10:25,057 --> 00:10:30,620
据说这个女孩是森林女巫的孩子
It is said the girl is the child of a forest witch.

94
00:10:30,756 --> 00:10:33,263
我见过她 独自一人在乡间小路上徘徊
I've seen her, wandering the back roads alone

95
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:35,122
她手臂上停着一只鹰
with a hawk on her arm.

96
00:10:35,258 --> 00:10:37,091
休兰兹有鹰吗？
A hawk at Hewlands?

97
00:10:37,226 --> 00:10:39,003
是的
Yes.

98
00:10:39,139 --> 00:10:41,836
他们说她独自一人带他去了森林
They say she takes him to the forest with her unaccompanied.

99
00:10:41,972 --> 00:10:44,172
是啊 但是你确定吗 伊莱扎？
Yeah, but are you certain, Eliza?

100
00:10:44,308 --> 00:10:47,641
大女儿养的是鹰 而不是女仆？
The eldest daughter keeps a hawk, not a servant girl?

101
00:10:47,777 --> 00:10:49,846
是的没错
Yes. Yeah.

102
00:11:16,736 --> 00:11:17,808
艾格尼丝
Agnes.

103
00:11:22,445 --> 00:11:23,847
你好
Hello.

104
00:11:24,846 --> 00:11:26,547
你在这里做什么？
What are you doing here?

105
00:11:26,682 --> 00:11:28,379
给你带来了这个
Brought you this.

106
00:11:29,849 --> 00:11:31,112
那是什么？
What is it?

107
00:11:31,247 --> 00:11:32,886
呃……
It's, uh...

108
00:11:33,021 --> 00:11:35,155
这是给你的鸟儿准备的新手套
it's a new glove for your bird.

109
00:11:36,625 --> 00:11:38,224
我有一只手套
I have a glove.

110
00:11:44,962 --> 00:11:45,994
艾格尼丝
Agnes.

111
00:11:47,702 --> 00:11:49,400
艾格尼丝 等等
Agnes, wait.

112
00:11:54,513 --> 00:11:56,004
我知道你是谁
I know who you are.

113
00:11:56,139 --> 00:11:57,873
我是谁？
Who am I?

114
00:11:58,008 --> 00:12:00,112
嗯 我……我不认识你 但我听说过一些事……
Well, I... I don't know you, but I've heard things...

115
00:12:00,248 --> 00:12:01,919
我是森林女巫的女儿？
I'm the daughter of a forest witch?

116
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:03,686
是的 人们都这么说 但我不在乎……
Yes. People say that, but I-I don't care...

117
00:12:03,821 --> 00:12:06,349
我是我母亲的女儿
I am my mother's daughter.

118
00:12:06,485 --> 00:12:08,760
我从她身上学到了很多东西
I've learnt many things from her.

119
00:12:11,728 --> 00:12:12,890
你在看什么？
What are you looking at?

120
00:12:13,026 --> 00:12:14,260
你——为什么？
- You. - Why?

121
00:12:20,732 --> 00:12:23,601
我……我以为你是一位能言善辩的人 我的导师
I... -I thought you were a man of words, master tutor.

122
00:12:23,737 --> 00:12:25,741
是的
Yes.

123
00:12:25,876 --> 00:12:27,604
难道不是吗？
Are you not?

124
00:12:27,739 --> 00:12:31,145
我有时觉得和人交流很困难
Speaking with people is sometimes difficult for me.

125
00:12:32,508 --> 00:12:34,786
那你就给我讲个故事吧
Well, tell me a story, then.

126
00:12:35,753 --> 00:12:37,822
——一个故事？——是的
- A story? - Yes.

127
00:12:40,186 --> 00:12:42,453
你想听什么样的故事？
What story would you like?

128
00:12:49,899 --> 00:12:52,298
让你感动的事物
Something that moves you.

129
00:12:55,935 --> 00:12:57,567
好的
All right.

130
00:12:59,308 --> 00:13:02,506
你知道俄耳甫斯和欧律狄刻的故事吗？
Do you know the story of Orpheus and Eurydice?

131
00:13:05,508 --> 00:13:09,084
奥菲斯是一位音乐家
Orpheus is a man of music.

132
00:13:10,084 --> 00:13:12,485
他有一副非常动听的嗓音
He has this exquisite voice.

133
00:13:13,421 --> 00:13:16,492
他演奏的基塔拉琴 是一种……
His playing of the kithara, which is a...

134
00:13:16,628 --> 00:13:18,262
它是一种类似竖琴的里拉琴
is-is a harp-like lyre,

135
00:13:18,398 --> 00:13:21,595
真是太神圣了
is so divine,

136
00:13:21,731 --> 00:13:24,594
鸟类 那……
birds, the...

137
00:13:24,729 --> 00:13:27,134
野兽 甚至石头和树木
the beasts, e-even the stones and the trees,

138
00:13:27,270 --> 00:13:32,109
他们都随着他的音乐节奏舞动起来
they all moved to the rhythm of his music.

139
00:13:32,245 --> 00:13:37,140
现在 俄耳甫斯爱上了这位美丽的仙女欧律狄刻
Now, Orpheus falls in love with this beautiful nymph, Eurydice.

140
00:13:37,276 --> 00:13:40,178
他们结婚后不久
Soon after their marriage,

141
00:13:40,313 --> 00:13:42,017
欧律狄刻被毒蛇咬了
Eurydice's bitten by a viper

142
00:13:42,152 --> 00:13:45,016
毒素在她体内蔓延
and poison courses through her body,

143
00:13:45,151 --> 00:13:46,653
她被杀了
and she's killed.

144
00:13:48,826 --> 00:13:51,357
而奥尔甫斯 悲痛欲绝
And Orpheus, filled with grief,

145
00:13:51,493 --> 00:13:54,525
前往冥界将她带回来
journeys to the underworld to take her back.

146
00:13:55,694 --> 00:13:59,935
他迷住了这只三头犬 刻耳柏洛斯
He charms this three-headed dog, Cerberus.

147
00:14:00,071 --> 00:14:03,798
他迷惑了哈迪斯 直到最后……
He beguiles Hades until finally...

148
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:06,876
他可以把他的爱人带回去
...he's allowed to take his love back with him

149
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:09,540
对生者的世界而言 但是……
to the world of the living but...

150
00:14:11,342 --> 00:14:12,712
……但有一个条件
...under one condition.

151
00:14:12,847 --> 00:14:14,611
那是什么？
What is it?

152
00:14:15,754 --> 00:14:17,185
她必须跟在他后面
She must follow behind him,

153
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:20,254
他绝对不能回头看她
and he must not turn around to look at her.

154
00:14:23,587 --> 00:14:27,328
现在 当他们开始攀登时
Now, as they begin their ascent,

155
00:14:27,464 --> 00:14:31,199
奥菲斯听不到她的脚步声 所以他侧耳倾听……
Orpheus can't hear her footsteps, so he listens...

156
00:14:32,896 --> 00:14:36,998
……然后听啊听啊听
...and listens and listens and listens.

157
00:14:38,837 --> 00:14:42,771
但他只能听到自己的心跳声
But all he can hear is the sound of his heartbeat.

158
00:14:49,688 --> 00:14:51,890
其余时间一片寂静
And the rest is silence.

159
00:14:55,822 --> 00:14:59,293
当他接近冥界之门时……
And as he approaches the gates of the underworld...

160
00:15:03,829 --> 00:15:05,629
他再也无法控制自己了
...he can't contain himself any longer.

161
00:15:05,764 --> 00:15:08,907
他转过身去看她 而她……
He turns around to look at her, and she is...

162
00:15:10,669 --> 00:15:12,977
永远被困在冥界
...trapped in the underworld forever.

163
00:15:27,385 --> 00:15:29,087
唔
Hmm.

164
00:15:29,222 --> 00:15:30,955
那真是一个好故事
That was a good story.

165
00:15:31,090 --> 00:15:32,931
你喜欢它吗？
Did you like it?

166
00:15:37,468 --> 00:15:40,429
艾草啊 记住你所带来的一切
Remember, mugwort, what you brought to pass,

167
00:15:40,565 --> 00:15:42,798
你在Regenmeld准备了什么
what you readied at Regenmeld.

168
00:15:42,933 --> 00:15:47,040
你的名字叫乌娜 是最古老的植物
You're called Una, the most ancient plant.

169
00:15:47,175 --> 00:15:49,803
你敢违抗三 你敢违抗三十
You defy three, you defy 30,

170
00:15:49,939 --> 00:15:51,939
你无惧毒液 你无惧空气传播疾病
you defy venom, you defy air illness,

171
00:15:52,074 --> 00:15:54,609
你对抗着潜伏在这片土地上的恐怖
you defy the horror that stalks the land.

172
00:15:54,744 --> 00:15:57,615
还有你 路边面包 植物之母
And you, waybread, plant mother,

173
00:15:57,750 --> 00:16:00,420
你面向东方 内心却无比强大
you're open to the east yet mighty within.

174
00:16:00,555 --> 00:16:04,919
马车从你身上缓缓驶过 女人们骑马从你身上经过
Carts creeped over you, women rode over you.

175
00:16:05,054 --> 00:16:07,792
你挺过了这一切 并且进行了反击
You withstood it all, and you pushed back.

176
00:16:07,928 --> 00:16:11,162
你真的了解一个人的一切吗？
Is it true that you know everything about a person

177
00:16:11,297 --> 00:16:13,296
通过触摸这里？
by touching them here?

178
00:16:13,431 --> 00:16:14,797
并非全部
Not everything.

179
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:16,936
当你触摸我这里的时候 你看到了什么？
When you touched me here, what did you see?

180
00:16:17,071 --> 00:16:18,634
我看到了一幅风景
I saw a landscape.

181
00:16:18,769 --> 00:16:20,902
- 你看到了风景？ - 嗯
- You saw a landscape? - Mm-hmm.

182
00:16:22,741 --> 00:16:27,816
太空、洞穴、悬崖顶、
Spaces, caves, cliff tops,

183
00:16:27,952 --> 00:16:31,349
隧道和海洋
tunnels and oceans,

184
